==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} [[#Latin|infimum]] ‘lowest part’, from [[infimus]] ‘lowest’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ɪnˈfaɪməm/}} (''UK'')

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|infima}}

#{{mathematics}} (''of a subset'') the [[greatest]] [[element]] that is [[smaller]] than all other elements of the subset

===Synonyms===
*[[greatest lower bound]]

